Package a4

Interface PriorityQueue<E,​P>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Heap
    public interface PriorityQueue<E,​P>
    A priority queue stores elements of type E with priorities of type P (typically P is Integer or Double). This particular interface also only allows one copy of a given element to be stored. That is, if you try to add an element e where e.equals(f) for some f in this, add will throw an exception. In the efficiency requirements below, n refers to this.size(). For example, poll() says it should run in O(log n) time; this means it should run in time logarithmic in the number of elements in the queue.
